docs.lead_paragraph: HEALTH OF THE FRENCH MINISTER,-The friends of M. DE SARTIGES, the French Minister, are much distressed at learning that he has been pronounced by the physicians at Plombieres to be in a very dangerous state of health. An enlargement of the liver in combination with an inflammation of the spleen threatens the most serious consequences.

headline.main: EUROPEAN NEWS.; RELATIONS OF FRANCE AND ENGLAND. American Securities in London. Views of Napoleon III. on the Italian Question. ARRIVAL OF THE OCEAN QUEEN. PROGRESS OF THE ZURICH CONFERENCE.

docs.lead_paragraph: The United States Mail steamship Occan Queen, Capt. SEABURY, from Southampton at 2 o'clock on the afternoon of Aug. 31, arrived at this port last evening. Her advices have been anticipated by dispatches received fran her off Cape Race, and by the arrival at Quebec of the Anglo Saxon, which sailed from Liverpool on the same day.

docs.snippet: We have an exciting rumor, this morning, to the effect that the British war steamer Satellite has bombarded the United States military station recently established upon San Juan Island. The story comes in a round about way, and is probably false.

docs.lead_paragraph: We have an exciting rumor, this morning, to the effect that the British war steamer Satellite has bombarded the United States military station recently established upon San Juan Island. The story comes in a round about way, and is probably false.
